<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-25T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-25T22:00:00-05:00" n="695" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d695">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13238: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Josselyn</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-26T11:00:00+08:00">October 26, 1935—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 26—9:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>54. My number 51, October 7, 4 p.m., paragraph 3. Missionary party
                            arrived safely Paotow Suiyuan Province yesterday according to a telegram
                            received by mission headquarters here today. Repeated to the Department,
                            Peiping, Nanking.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Josselyn</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>